These samples demonstrate basic concepts and principles of DynamicScript

1. Description
================
helloworld - your first script;
composition - lambda composition;
async - asynchronous language support at syntax level;
debug - demonstates command-line debugger;
polymorph - demonstrates interpretation of language expressions as first-class objects.

2. How to run
================
The first, you should build DynamicScript Interpreter.

WINDOWS
	1. Specify location of DynamicScript Interpreter;
		SET DSI = D:\DynamicScript\csharp\bin\dsi.exe
	2. Change directory to the folder with samples;
		cd D:\DynamicScript\samples
	3. Specify location of script file for interpreter;
		%DSI% -e helloworld\program.ds
LINUX
	1. Specify location of DynamicScript Interpreter;
		export DSI = ~/DynamicScript/csharp/bin/dsi.exe
	2. Specify location of Mono executable;
		export MONO=/opt/mono/bin/mono
	3. Change directory to the folder with samples;
		cd ~/DynamicScript/samples
	4. Specify location of script file for interpreter;
		$MONO $DSI -e helloworld/program.ds